    a word. Did she just leave now or did she confront him, demanding an explanation? <br>
<br>
    She sat there for what seemed like hours, pondering the choices before her. Feeling again the pain that his<br>
    leaving had caused her. Several more times, she saw him chasing orc slavers down the passage past her<br>
    but she remained concealed. <br>
<br>
    Finally deciding that if he wished to see her, he knew the places to look, she stood to leave. At just that<br>
    moment, another wounded orc rounded the corner. Just as Marina stepped out of the shadows, she was<br>
    knocked to the ground with a heavy weight on top of her. Looking up, she was face to face with Cerawyn,<br>
    his look of surprise mirroring her own. <br>
<br>
    Leaning down, he kissed her once, pulled back looking into her eyes, and then kissed her again. Standing,<br>
    he helped her to her feet, saying &quot;I never thought I'd be able to do that again.&quot; <br>
<br>
    Marina just stood there, looking at him, unsure of what to feel. Cerawyn took her hand and led her deeper<br>
    into the caves. &quot;I'm waiting for Kelynn to show up. I have to get some information from him for the guild.&quot; <br>
<br>
    Marina started a slow burn. Once again he had put Scout's business ahead of her. If not for the message<br>
    from the unknown person, she still wouldn't know he was here. <br>
<br>
    Sitting down with her back against the wall, she looked at Cerawyn and said simply &quot;Why?&quot; Cerawyn<br>
    sighed. He had hoped to have more time with her before he had to explain where he had gone and why. <br>
<br>
    &quot;You remember me telling of my mother's murder?&quot; <br>
<br>
    Marina nodded her head, looking confused. What did his mother have to do with his leaving? <br>
<br>
    &quot;Living with you, loving you, I saw how happy my parents had been. It began to eat at me that their time<br>
    together had been cut short by the Circle of the Unseen Hands. I decided it was time for me to have my<br>
    revenge. I traveled to Qeynos and managed to get into the guildhall or so I thought. It was a trap. The<br>
    guild leader is a paranoid devil but this time it paid off for him. I was captured and thrown into a cell. I was<br>
    kept in that cell until about a month ago when I managed to escape.&quot; <br>
<br>
    &quot;But why didn't you tell me?&quot; <br>
<br>
    &quot;You wouldn't have let me go alone. If I hadn't taken you with me, you would have followed me. I couldn't<br>
    allow you to be harmed. That is why I didn't come straight to you when I escaped. If they had decided to<br>
    come after me, I couldn't risk you.&quot; <br>
<br>
    Cerawyn knelt next to Marina, running his fingertips over her features. &quot;You are my heart, I won't ever<br>
    allow anyone to harm you.&quot; <br>
<br>
    Tears rolled down Marina's face, &quot;I thought you had left me.&quot; <br>
<br>
    &quot;Never, my little one. It was thoughts of you that kept me going, that kept me seeking a way out. Will you<br>
    forgive me for leaving?&quot; <br>
<br>
    &quot;Do you promise to never do anything so stupid as that again?&quot; Cerawyn nodded. Marina reached up and<br>
    pulled his face down to hers. &quot;Then aye, I forgive you. But if you ever do anything like that again, I'll kill<br>
    you myself&quot; she whispered. <br>
<br>
    Cerawyn chuckled and then leaned in to kiss his wife.  <p>Luck in the Shadows,<br>
